They are regulars on the start line of the Cape classic and have added medals to their cycling accomplishments. They are encouraging riders of all abilities to join in the cause. “Whenever Rachel and I cycle, we wear our Cow cycling outfits. When people see two Cows on a tandem riding along the road, we immediately create a spectacle. “People stop us to chat and ask about our strange cycling attire. “We are black and white, wearing black and white Cow lycra, which many people see as a symbol of racial harmony and social cohesion. “Rachel is a proud cowgirl and I’m a proud cowboy,” Dali said. The Tambos have implored people to grow the numbers of The Cows herd in the Cape Town Cycle Tour. For more information about the cows, visit www.thecows.co.za